1998 - 12-28
Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Monday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- The government has decided to call in the central armed forces in the Capital in wake of murders in the city .
The Times of India :
-- Sri Lankan President Chandrika Kumaratunga arrived here Sunday on her three-day official visit to India .
The Statesman :
-- A five-year-old boy was shot dead and cash worth 70,000 rupees ( 1,641.27 U.S. dollars ) and jewelry was taken away by five armed robbers who entered an east Delhi house late Sunday evening .
The Economic Times :
-- The United States has agreed to revoke the ban imposed on import of shrimps from India .
